    <!-- Hotkey info tooltips — "when is this useful?" copy shown under
         the info (i) icon next to each row. Longer than the one-line
         description; written so a first-time user understands the
         in-game situation the shortcut helps with. -->
    <sys:String x:Key="Hotkey_9000_Info" xmlns:sys="clr-namespace:System;assembly=mscorlib">The core on/off switch. Press once to begin watching the dialogue area and translating what appears; press again to stop when the cutscene or quest is over. Equivalent to the big "Start" button on the Dashboard — use the shortcut when you don't want to alt-tab out of the game.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Hotkey_9001_Info" xmlns:sys="clr-namespace:System;assembly=mscorlib">Redraws the rectangle Kaption watches for dialogue. Use this after moving the game to a different monitor, changing resolution, toggling windowed/fullscreen, or any time subtitles stop appearing even though dialogue is happening on screen.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Hotkey_9002_Info" xmlns:sys="clr-namespace:System;assembly=mscorlib">Instantly hides the overlay subtitle box without stopping translation. Useful for screenshots, cinematic moments, or when a UI element overlaps with the subtitle. Press again to bring it back — translation keeps running in the background either way.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Hotkey_9003_Info" xmlns:sys="clr-namespace:System;assembly=mscorlib">Flashes a coloured outline where Kaption is currently watching for dialogue. Use it to verify your capture region is still aligned with the game's dialogue box after a resolution or UI change.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Hotkey_9004_Info" xmlns:sys="clr-namespace:System;assembly=mscorlib">Forces an immediate re-translation of the current frame, even if the text hasn't changed. Useful when Kaption is stuck on an outdated line (e.g. the typewriter animation moved on but the match didn't update), or when you want to re-translate after tweaking a setting without stopping and starting translation.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Hotkey_9005_Info" xmlns:sys="clr-namespace:System;assembly=mscorlib">Draws a one-shot rectangle anywhere on screen — an item tooltip, a quest title, a menu entry — and pops a translation next to it. Independent of your main dialogue region, so it works for UI text that isn't dialogue.</sys:String>

